This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10 (Android 15 / API 35+), **edge-to-edge is enforced** and `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` is deprecated/ignored.

The modern fix is to react to **window insets** so your layout automatically pads itself when the IME (keyboard) appears. Two main approaches:

---

### Option 1: Set `android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"` + use `Fit…` system bars (simplest)

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
[Activity(WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize, /* ... */)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then in `OnCreate`, tell the decor view to fit system windows:

```csharp
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    if (OperatingSystem.IsAndroidVersionAtLeast(35))
    {
        // Opt into the edge-to-edge inset handling
        AndroidX.Core.View.ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView, new WindowInsetsListener());
    }
}

private class WindowInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object,
    AndroidX.Core.View.IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(
        Android.Views.View v,
        AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(
            AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var systemBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(
            AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Use whichever bottom inset is larger (keyboard vs nav bar)
        int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, systemBarInsets.Bottom);

        v.SetPadding(
            systemBarInsets.Left, systemBarInsets.Top,
            systemBarInsets.Right, bottomPadding);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

This makes the entire window content resize when the keyboard opens, pushing your input bar up.

---

### Option 2: Per-page `Margin` binding (lighter touch)

If you only need it on the chat page, listen to insets and bind the page's bottom margin in your XAML:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

---

### Key takeaways

| .NET 9 | .NET 10+ (API 35) |
|---|---|
| `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` | Deprecated / no-op |
| System handled resize | You handle `WindowInsets` (IME type) |

**Option 1** is the closest drop-in replacement for the old behavior and works app-wide. Make sure you have the `AndroidX.Core` NuGet (it's included by default in MAUI projects).
